rComments: Absolutely AMAZING prof. Shes soooo caring and explains concepts very well. She doesn't bell curve, but she gave extra credit assignments so our final mark could have been increased by an extra 6%! She's not the easiest marker but you will learn from her class and it'll help you a lot in the future. Shes also really easy to talk to.

She is really one of the best lecturers I have ever had. Her lectures are clear and she gives quizzes near the end of them but they are straightforward if you pay attention. She makes enough time for her students ( she went live on insta night before final exam!). This class is an easy 4.0 if you're willing to put in the effort.

Awesome prof, clearly passionate about music cognition research and cares that her students do well. Course isn't all about memorizing information, so you end up learning a lot about the field without getting overwhelmed. Course consisted of quizzes on the assigned readings, a big assignment (instead of a midterm), a research poster and final.
